Singer, Yemi Alade, has recounted her first time of meeting late actress, Ada Ameh.



In a tribute to Ameh, who died on Sunday evening in Warri, the singer revealed she was having a bad day and the actress made her feel better.



Alade shared a video from their shoot, which she captioned, “I was having a bad day the first time I met you and I don’t know if anyone noticed but YOU instantly made me FEEL good.



“I thanked you over and over again! You didn’t have to but you did! Most people will avoid it or act like I have a problem with them! Sigh…



“This is how I will always remember you! Thank you for blessing me Mama Ada Ameh.”



